The paper deals with automatic keyphrase extraction, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of statistical association among candidate keyphrases, measured using web mining, suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks (cs.DL) in related work. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL.
